TODO: Optimize optional field transformations with do ? expressions

Current code in generated models uses verbose switch expressions for optional fields:

```motoko
availability_status = switch (json.availability_status) {
    case (?v) AvailabilityEnum.fromJSON(v);
    case null null
};
```

This pattern appears throughout generated models when converting optional enum fields
from JSON-facing to user-facing types.

OPTIMIZATION: Use do ? expressions for cleaner, more idiomatic Motoko:

```motoko
availability_status = do ? { AvailabilityEnum.fromJSON(json.availability_status!)! };
```

The do ? block automatically propagates null values:
- If json.availability_status is null, the first ! returns null, block returns null
- If fromJSON returns null, the second ! returns null, block returns null
- If both succeed, returns the unwrapped value

Benefits:
- More concise and readable
- Idiomatic Motoko (follows Option monad pattern)
- Reduces boilerplate in generated code
- Same runtime behavior (null propagation)

Implementation:
- Update model.mustache template (lines ~135, ~145, ~166, ~170, ~195)
- Change switch expression pattern to do ? block
- Applies to both toJSON and fromJSON conversions
- Only affects optional fields with enum/model conversions

Files affected:
- modules/openapi-generator/src/main/resources/motoko/model.mustache
- All generated model files with optional enum/model fields

Pattern locations in template:
```mustache
{{^required}}switch (value.{{name}}) { case (?v) ?{{{datatypeWithEnum}}}.toJSON(v); case null null }{{/required}}
{{^required}}switch (json.{{name}}) { case (?v) {{{datatypeWithEnum}}}.fromJSON(v); case null null }{{/required}}
```

Optimized pattern:
```mustache
{{^required}}do ? { {{{datatypeWithEnum}}}.toJSON(value.{{name}}!)! }{{/required}}
{{^required}}do ? { {{{datatypeWithEnum}}}.fromJSON(json.{{name}}!)! }{{/required}}
```

Priority: Low (optimization, not a bug)
Impact: All generated models with optional enum/model fields
